OL,4,COrphaned boy told he can stay in UK
OL,5,Cpermanently
OL,6, A 13-year-old boy who faced deportation
OL,7, from Glasgow to Georgia after being
OL,8, orphaned has been told he can stay in
OL,9, the UK permanently.
OL,11,FGiorgi Kakava moved to Scotland with
OL,12,Fhis mother Sophie when he was three,
OL,13,Fafter his father was killed.
OL,15,FWhen his mother died three years ago,
OL,16,FGiorgi faced being sent back but was
OL,17,Fgranted temporary asylum.
OL,19,FWhile he has been told he can now stay
OL,20,Findefinitely, his grandmother has only
OL,21,Fbeen given 30 months leave to remain.
